87</ref>\n***Cold Iron Studios\n* [[Endemol Shine Group]] - sold to [[Banijay Group]]\n* [[TrueX]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-looks-to-sell-truex-ad-tech-firm-it-absorbed-from-fox-11584481326|title=Disney Looks to Sell TrueX, Ad-Tech Firm It Absorbed From Fox|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|last=Patel|first=Sahil|date=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Venture capital holdings sold===\n* Iridigm Display Corporation: acquired by Qualcomm, Inc., September, 2004\n* Kyte: acquired by KIT Digital, January 2011\n* Move Networks: December 2010 acquisition of EchoStar\n* PopularMedia: acquired by StrongMail, June 2009\n* Pure Digital Technologies: [[Cisco]] acquisition in May 2009\n* Quigo: acquired by AOL December 2007\n* Rosum: sold to TruePosition in December 2010\n* Scrapblog: sold to Mixbook December 2010\n* Sometrics: acquired by [[American Express]], September 2011<ref name=sb/>\n* [[56.com]]: sold to Renren in September, 2011\n* Youxigu: Steamboat sold its stake to Tencent Holdings Ltd. in March 2010<ref name=sbc/>\n\n===Dormant or shuttered===\nThe following companies are subsidiaries of Disney that either are no longer active or have been absorbed into another part of the company.\n<!-- don't add 21st/20th Century Fox units closed before 2019 as they are not Disney units -->\n* [[ABC Kids (United States)|ABC Kids]]: Replaced by [[Litton's Weekend Adventure]].\n* [[Americast]]: Telephone digital TV joint venture\n* [[Anaheim Sports]], Inc.: Formerly Disney Sports Enterprises, Inc.\n* [[Arena Football League]]: ESPN bought a minority share of the league in December 2006; the league ceased operations in July 2009. The AFL was revived in 2010, but is a separate legal entity from the original, with no Disney ownership.\n* [[Avalanche Software]]: Closed in May 2016 and re-opened and acquired by [[Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment]] in January 2017.\n* [[Black Rock Studio]]\n* [[Blip (website)|Blip Networks, Inc.]]: Acquired by Maker Studios (Now Disney Digital Network) in August 2013,.<ref name=\"thewrap\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/maker-studios-acquires-web-series-developer-and-distributor-blip/|title=Maker Studios Acquires Web Series Developer and Distributor Blip|work=TheWrap|access-date=2018-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181130155110/https://www.thewrap.com/maker-studios-acquires-web-series-developer-and-distributor-blip/|archive-date=2018-11-30|url-status=live}}</ref> Shut down in August 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/digital/news/maker-studios-is-shutting-down-blip-next-month-1201544219/|title=Maker Studios Is Shutting Down Blip Next Month|last=Roettgers|first=Janko|date=2015-07-20|language=en-US|access-date=2016-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160722083815/http://variety.com/2015/digital/news/maker-studios-is-shutting-down-blip-next-month-1201544219/|archive-date=2016-07-22|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Bonnie View Productions, Ltd.:<ref name=dta/> Production company for \"Crusaders\", a syndicated news magazine show\n* Buena Vista Visual Effects\n* Cal Publishing: Cal Publishing was a subsidiary created by Disney to acquire the assets of [[CrossGen]]. After the acquisition, both companies were folded into [[Disney Publishing Worldwide]]. Disney subsidiary [[Marvel Comics]] has since announced that it will revive CrossGen as an imprint.\n* Canasa Trading Corp.<ref name=dta/>\n* [[Caravan Pictures]]<ref name=dta>{{cite web|title=DETERMINATION|url=http://www.nysdta.org/Determinations/818378.det.htm|work=DISNEY ENTERPRISES, INC.|publisher=State of New York DIVISION OF TAX APPEALS|accessdate=December 4, 2012}}</ref>\n* Disney [[Circle 7 Animation]]\n* [[DisneyToon Studios]]\n* [[Club Disney]]: Creation of [[Disney Regional Entertainment]], Club Disney had 5 locations built in the U.S. All 5 locations were closed in November 1999.\n* [[Walt Disney Feature Animation Florida]], Inc.<ref name=dta/>\n* [[Disney Auctions]]\n* [[Disney Comics (publishing)|Disney Comics]]\n* [[Disney Interactive Studios]]\n* [[Disney Development Company]]: Construct arm<ref>{{cite news|last=DICKERSON|first=MARLA|title=Seaside Synergy in Surf City|url=https://articles.latimes.com/1996-02-15/business/fi-36390_1_hilton-grand-vacations|accessdate=December 13, 2012|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|publisher=Times Mirror Company|date=February 15, 1996|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150712211006/http://articles.latimes.com/1996-02-15/business/fi-36390_1_hilton-grand-vacations|archive-date=2015-07-12|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Disney Regional Entertainment]]: Ran [[Disney Quest]] and the [[ESPN Zone]] Restaurant/entertainment chains. The division was closed in June 2010. Two ESPN Zones remain operating, but now as local franchises.\n* Disney TeleVentures, Inc.: [[Americast]] telco venture programming and technical support<ref name=dta/>\n* Disney Television and Telecommunications, division group (not to be confused with Walt Disney Television production division) eliminated after Disney-CC/ABC merger<ref>{{cite press release|title=Roth, Iger Assume Expanded Responsibilities at the Walt Disney Company|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/ROTH%2c+IGER+ASSUME+EXPANDED+RESPONSIBILITIES+AT+THE+WALT+DISNEY+COMPANY-a018198127|accessdate=March 11, 2013|agency=PR Newswire|publisher=The Walt Disney Company|date=April 16, 1996|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925165739/http://www.thefreelibrary.com/ROTH%2c+IGER+ASSUME+EXPANDED+RESPONSIBILITIES+AT+THE+WALT+DISNEY+COMPANY-a018198127|archive-date=September 25, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Dream Quest Images]]: Merged with Disney Features Animation computer group to form The Secret Lab\n* DreamWorks II Distribution Co. LLC, film rights acquired from [[DreamWorks Pictures|DreamWorks]] and [[Reliance Entertainment|Reliance]].''<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ftc.gov/enforcement/premerger-notification-program/early-termination-notices/20160358|title=20160358: The Walt Disney Company; Steven Spielberg|date=December 11, 2015|publisher=Federal Trade Commission|accessdate=April 29, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160604055248/https://www.ftc.gov/enforcement/premerger-notification-program/early-termination-notices/20160358|archive-date=June 4, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ftc.gov/enforcement/premerger-notification-program/early-termination-notices/20160359|title=20160359: The Walt Disney Company; Anil D. Ambani|date=December 11, 2015|publisher=Federal Trade Commission|accessdate=April 29, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160604045757/https://www.ftc.gov/enforcement/premerger-notification-program/early-termination-notices/20160359|archive-date=June 4, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>''\n* [[DreamWorks Television]] (1994-2002): Joint venture of CC/ABC with [[DreamWorks Pictures|DreamWorks]] which was dissolved at the end of the seven-year agreement<ref>{{cite book|last1=Kunz|first1=William M.|title=Culture Conglomerates: Consolidation in the Motion Picture and Television Industries|date=2007|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|isbn=9780742540668|pages=49, 50|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OMD4bqQg4iAC&pg=PA49&lpg=PA49&dq=Touchstone+Television&source=bl&ots=2v2KE0kylk&sig=g5UEe1DIOF2wzJD53QLuwbXj0RI&hl=en&sa=X&ei=MpePU8_ILdSUqAa0oYGYAw&ved=0CEEQ6AEwBzg8#v=onepage&q=Touchstone%20Television&f=false|accessdate=June 4, 2014|chapter=2|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140709030518/http://books.google.com/books?id=OMD4bqQg4iAC&pg=PA49&lpg=PA49&dq=Touchstone+Television&source=bl&ots=2v2KE0kylk&sig=g5UEe1DIOF2wzJD53QLuwbXj0RI&hl=en&sa=X&ei=MpePU8_ILdSUqAa0oYGYAw&ved=0CEEQ6AEwBzg8#v=onepage&q=Touchstone%20Television&f=false|archive-date=July 9, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[ESPN The Magazine]]\n* Faded Denim Productions Ltd.: Defunct production company\n* [[Fall Line Studios]]\n* Fidelity Television, Inc.: owned [[KCAL-TV]]\n** KHJ-TV, Inc.<ref name=dta/>\n*Fox Research Library\n*Fogbank Entertainment - shuttered in 2020<ref>https://venturebeat.com/2020/01/24/disney-will-close-foxnexts-fogbank-entertainment-game-studio/</ref>\n*FoxNext VR Studio - shuttered in 2020\n*FoxNext Destinations - shuttered in 2019\n** [[20th Century Fox World (Malaysia)|20th Century Fox World Malaysia]] (license to [[Genting Highlands|Resort World]] by [[Genting Group]])\n* [[Walt Disney World Hospitality and Recreation Corporation|Harvest Groves, Inc.]]: Merged\n* Hollywood Basic: Sub-label of [[Hollywood Records]] that released rap music (including music by DJ Shadow and Organized Konfusion). The label was discontinued in the mid 1990s.\n* [[Hollywood Pictures]]: Film label of The Walt Disney Studios created in 1989 and shuttered in 2007.\n* Hollywood Pictures Music: Label of Disney Music Publishing that distributed songs from Hollywood Pictures' titles.\n* [[ImageMovers Digital]]: Closed in 2011 after the abysmal opening of ''[[Mars Needs Moms]]''.\n* [[Infoseek|Infoseek Corporation]]: Acquired by Disney in 1998 and merged into Disney's GO Network. The Infoseek name is no longer in use.\n* [[Jumbo Pictures]]: Acquired by Disney in 1996, Jumbo Pictures produced ''[[Doug (TV series)|Doug]]'', ''[[101 Dalmatians: The Series]]'', and ''[[PB&J Otter]]'' for Disney. The company was folded into [[Walt Disney Television Animation]].\n* [[Jetix Europe|Jetix Europe, N.V.]], formerly Fox Kids Europe: 73% acquired with FOX/ABC Family Worldwide, Inc. & held by BVS International, N.V.; full owner in 2009, ran 13 Jetix channels\n** [[GXT]]: Italian channel for older teens sold in management buy out of Jetix Italy. Closed in late 2014\n** [[K2 (TV channel)|K-2]]: Syndicated Italian block also sold in management buy out of Jetix Italy. \n** Jetix Consumer Products\n** Jetix Espa\u00f1a S.L.: Joint venture with Sogecable S.A. to operate Jetix Spain\n** Jetix Poland Limited: With minority owner, a subsidiary of United Pan-Europe Communications N.V.\n** TV10 B.V.: Joint venture with [[SBS Broadcasting]] B.V. to services the Dutch channel\n* [[Jetix Animation Concepts]]: Folded into [[Disney Television Animation|Walt Disney Television Animation]] in 2009.\n* [[Junction Point Studios]]\n* Kingdom Comics:<ref>{{cite news|last=Kit|first=Borys|title=Disney draws up plans for graphic novel biz|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/31/arts-disney-dc-idUSN2934100420080531|accessdate=October 3, 2012|periodical=The Hollywood Reporter|date=May 29, 2008|agency=Reuters|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130702001753/https://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/31/arts-disney-dc-idUSN2934100420080531|archive-date=2013-07-02|url-status=live}}</ref> The Kingdom Comics unit's creatives/executives moved its deal to an independent Monsterfoot Production.<ref>{{cite news|last=McNary|first=Dave|title=Facts on Pacts|url=https://www.variety.com/graphics/factsonpacts.pdf|accessdate=February 12, 2013|newspaper=Variety|year=2009|author2=Dana Harris|author3=Justin Kroll|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130319032300/http://www.variety.com/graphics/factsonpacts.pdf|archive-date=2013-03-19|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Walt Disney World Hospitality and Recreation Corporation|Lake Buena Vista Communities, Inc.]]\n* [[Lyric Street Records]]: Record label specializing in country music\n* [[Malibu Comics]]\n* [[Mammoth Records]]: Independent record label acquired by Disney in 1997\n* [[MLG Productions 1|MLG Productions 1 \u2013 MLG Productions 8]]: (Marvel's joint venture with Lionsgate) operationally defunct as the agreed upon number of DTV movies were finished\n* [[Pixar Canada]]: Opened in 2010,<ref>{{cite web |accessdate=April 20, 2010 |url=https://vancouversun.com/entertainment/movie-guide/Pixar+Canada+sets+home+base+Vancouver+looks+expand/2927398/story.html |title=Pixar Canada sets up home base in Vancouver, looks to expand |work=The Vancouver Sun |location=Canada |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100422042245/http://www.vancouversun.com/entertainment/movie-guide/Pixar%2BCanada%2Bsets%2Bhome%2Bbase%2BVancouver%2Blooks%2Bexpand/2927398/story.html |archivedate=April 22, 2010 |url-status=dead |df=mdy }}</ref> Closed in 2013.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://blogs.theprovince.com/2013/10/08/pixar-canada-shuts-its-doors-in-vancouver/ | title=Pixar Canada shuts its doors in Vancouver | work=[[The Province]] | date=October 8, 2013 | accessdate=October 8, 2013 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140424044457/http://blogs.theprovince.com/2013/10/08/pixar-canada-shuts-its-doors-in-vancouver/ | archive-date=April 24, 2014 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Propaganda Games]]: Shuttered in January 2011 after the development of ''[[Tron: Evolution]]'' was completed, and \n* [[Walt Disney World Company|Ranch and Grove Holding Corp.]]: Merged\n* Revelmode: Sub-network of Maker Studios (Now Disney Digital Network).<ref name=Spangler2016>{{cite web |last=Spangler |first=Todd |url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/pewdiepie-revelmode-network-1201678900/ |title=YouTube Megastar PewDiePie Launches 'Revelmode' Network |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=13 January 2016 |accessdate=19 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117224034/http://variety.com/2016/digital/news/pewdiepie-revelmode-network-1201678900/ |archivedate=17 January 2016 }}</ref> Shut down after [[PewDiePie]] was dropped because of [[Antisemitism|anti-semitic]] jokes made on his channel.<ref name=pdp>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/disney-pewdiepie-anti-semitic-videos-1201987380/|title=Disney's Maker Studios Drops PewDiePie Because of Anti-Semitic Videos|last=Roettgers|first=Janko|date=February 13, 2017|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=May 14, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215031419/http://variety.com/2017/digital/news/disney-pewdiepie-anti-semitic-videos-1201987380/|archive-date=February 15, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Dream Quest Images|The Secret Lab]]: Formed from Dream Quest Images & Walt Disney Features Animation computer group, closed in 2002\n* [[SIP Animation]] (Saban International Paris): 49% Minority stake owned by Disney. Separated from BVS Entertainment in 2001, renamed in 2002 and eventually filed for liquidation and closed in 2009. {{efn|Currently, [[The Walt Disney Company France]] acts as a contact point for this company and its former assets.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.snepmusique.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/ADHERER-AU-SNEP-.pdf |title=ADH\u00c9RER  AU  SNEP |author=<!--Not stated--> |publisher=[[SNEP]] |access-date=September 14, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828071145/http://www.snepmusique.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/ADHERER-AU-SNEP-.pdf |archive-date=August 28, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>}}\n* [[Skellington Productions]], Inc.: Production company formed between Walt Disney Feature Animation and filmmakers [[Tim Burton]] and [[Henry Selick]]\n* [[Soapnet]]: [[#Disney-ABC Television Group|DATG]] cable channel that closed on December 31, 2013\n* [[Starwave]]: Starwave was merged with Infoseek and acquired by Disney in 1998 to form GO Network. Starwave no longer operates as a stand-alone business. The label was recently resurrected to form Disney's Starwave Mobile which licenses content from third party companies for cell phone content.\n* [[Tapulous]]\n* [[Togetherville]]: Acquired in February 2011.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-19518_3-20036059-238.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2019-05-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026105937/http://news.cnet.com/8301-19518_3-20036059-238.html |archive-date=2012-10-26 |url-status=live }}</ref> Discontinued in March 2012.<ref>http://blog.togetherville.com/we-are-winding-down-togetherville/{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* [[Toontown Online]]: Servers were closed on September 19, 2013.\n* [[Touchstone Pictures]]: it was inactive in 2016. Label still used in home media distribution.\n* [[Touchwood Pacific Partners|Touchwood Pacific Partner]] 1, Inc. (not the limited partnership itself)<ref name=dta/>\n* Toysmart.com: Controlling interest<ref>{{cite news|last=Junnarkar|first=Sandeep|title=Disney plays the Net toy sales game|url=http://news.cnet.com/Disney-plays-the-Net-toy-sales-game/2100-1017_3-230245.html|accessdate=9 December 2012|newspaper=CNET News|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|date=August 25, 1999}}</ref>\n* [[UGC Fox Distribution]] (1995\u20132005)\n* [[Walt Disney Television (production company)]]: transferred to ABC Television Network, and later folded into Touchstone Television (now known as [[ABC Studios]])\n* [[WatchESPN]]: Shut down on July 1, 2019.\n* [[Wideload Games]]\n* Wizzer Productions, Inc.: Production company for the [[101 Dalmatians (1996 film)|''101 Dalmatians'']] 1996 live action movie.<ref name=dta/>\n** [[Club Penguin]]\n* [[Playdom]]\n* [[YourTV]] - Closed in 2019\n* Fox Consumer Products - Closed in 2020\n* [[Sony ESPN]] (50%, joint-venture with [[Sony]]) - Closed in 2020\n\n==See also==\n* [[Timeline of The Walt Disney Company]]\n* [[List of Disney animated universe characters]]\n* [[List of Pixar characters]]\n* [[List of Marvel Comics characters]]\n* [[List of Star Wars characters]]\n* [[Acquisition of 21st Century Fox by Disney]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{notelist}}\n\n{{Disney|state=expanded}}\n\n[[Category:Asset lists|Disney]]\n[[Category:Disney-related lists|Assets]]\n[[Category:The Walt Disney Company subsidiaries| ]]\n", "name_user": "2409:4043:797:e516::f2e:88a5", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eThe Walt Disney Company Latin America)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_assets_owned_by_The_Walt_Disney_Company"}
