dgar]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|{{dts|January 14, 1991}}<br />&ndash;<br />January 11, 1999<br><small>(not candidate for election)</small>\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|[[1990 Illinois gubernatorial election|1990]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"Kustra, Bob\"|[[Bob Kustra]]<br /><small>(resigned July 1, 1998)</small>\n|- style=\"height:2em;\"\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[1994 Illinois gubernatorial election|1994]]\n|- style=\"height:2em;\"\n|colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\"|''Vacant''\n|- style=\"height:2em;\"\n|39\n|data-sort-value=\"Ryan, George\"|[[File:2007 Governor George Ryan crop4 (cropped).JPG|75px]]\n!scope=\"row\"|[[George Ryan]]\n|{{dts|January 11, 1999}}<br />&ndash;<br />January 13, 2003<br><small>(not candidate for election)</small>\n|[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|[[1998 Illinois gubernatorial election|1998]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Republican Party (United States)/meta/color}}\"|\n|data-sort-value=\"Wood, Corinne\"|[[Corinne Wood]]\n|- style=\"height:2em;\"\n|rowspan=\"2\"|40\n|rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"Blagojevich, Rod\"|[[File:Rod Blagojevich (2911120436) (cropped).jpg|75px]]\n|rowspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"{{Democratic Party (United States)/meta/color}}\"|\n!scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"|[[Rod Blagojevich]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{dts|January 13, 2003}}<br />&ndash;<br />January 29, 2009<br><small>(impeached and removed)</small>{{efn|Blagojevich was impeached and removed from office on charges of corruption.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nga.org/cms/home/governors/past-governors-bios/page_illinois/col2-content/main-content-list/title_blagojevich_rod.default.html | title=Rod R. Blagojevich | publisher=[[National Governors Association]] | accessdate=June 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/30/us/30illinois.html | title=Blagojevich Ousted by Illinois State Senate | work=[[The New York Times]] | date=January 29, 2009 | accessdate=June 1, 2018}}</ref>}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Democratic Party (United